    "The inclusion of word embeddings allows the Fig. 1 Convolutional recurrent neural network AES architecture (Taghipour and Ng 2016) model to consider semantic information within the essay.",
    "However, this work still treated the essay text as a sequence of words.",
    "Document modeling using hierarchical architecture: Dong and Zhang (2016) proposed a two-layered CNN hierarchical architecture (Fig. 2) to capture word-level and sentence-level contexts from essays, aiming to model a document structure.",
    "In this architecture, the input essay is segmented into sentences (S 1,..., S n), with the first CNN layer capturing word- level contexts and the second CNN layer capturing sentence-level contexts.",
    "Expanding on this work, Dong et al. (2017) proposed an AES architecture that utilizes CNN, LSTM and attention mechanisms to model document structure."
